claim.claim-text:
13. An active matrix display device comprising: 
an active matrix circuit formed over a substrate; 
a signal line driving circuit formed over the substrate; 
a scan line driving circuit formed over the substrate; 
wherein each of the signal line driving circuit and the scan line driving circuit comprises a plurality of thin film transistors, each of the plurality of thin film transistors comprise: 
a semiconductor island having a first surface and a second surface opposed to the first surface; 
a first gate electrode adjacent to the first surface of the semiconductor island with a first gate insulating film interposed therebetween; and 
a second gate electrode adjacent to the second surface of the semiconductor island with a second gate insulating film interposed therebetween; and 

a circuit including a variable resistor, connected to the second gate electrode.

19. An active matrix display device comprising: 
an active matrix circuit formed over a substrate; 
a signal line driving circuit formed over the substrate; 
a scan line driving circuit formed over the substrate; 
wherein each of the signal line driving circuit and the scan line driving circuit comprises a plurality of thin film transistors, each of the plurality of thin film transistors comprise: 
a first gate electrode formed over a substrate; 
a semiconductor island adjacent to the first gate electrode with a first gate insulating film interposed therebetween; and 
a second gate electrode adjacent to the semiconductor island with a second gate insulating film interposed therebetween; and 

a circuit including a variable resistor, connected to the second gate electrode.

25. An inverter comprising: 
a first p-channel thin film transistor over a substrate: 
a second p-channel thin film transistor over the substrate; 
a first n-channel thin film transistor over the substrate; 
a second n-channel thin film transistor over the substrate, 
wherein each of the first and second p-channel thin film transistors and the first and second n-channel thin film transistors comprise: 
a semiconductor island having a first surface and a second surface opposed to the first surface; 
a first gate electrode adjacent to the first surface of the semiconductor island with a first gate insulating film interposed therebetween; and 
a second gate electrode adjacent to the second surface of the semiconductor island with a second gate insulating film interposed therebetween; and 

a circuit including a variable resistor, connected to the second gate electrode.

31. An inverter comprising: 
a first p-channel thin film transistor over a substrate: 
a second p-channel thin film transistor over the substrate; 
a first n-channel thin film transistor over the substrate; 
a second n-channel thin film transistor over the substrate, 
wherein each of the first and second p-channel thin film transistors and the first and second n-channel thin film transistors comprise: 
a first gate electrode formed over a substrate; 
a semiconductor island adjacent to the first gate electrode with a first gate insulating film interposed therebetween; and 
a second gate electrode adjacent to the semiconductor island with a second gate insulating film interposed therebetween; and 

a circuit including a variable resistor, connected to the second gate electrode.
